headline.print_headline: Ghosts of Ethnic Conflicts Past Haunt Fiji Vote
headline.main: Ghosts of Ethnic Conflicts Past Haunt Fiji Vote

lead_paragraph: When voters in Fiji head to the polls on Wednesday for the first time in eight years, they will be voting not only for a leader, but also testing the success of one of their military junta's key justifications: ending a history of ethnic conflict.
